OL,3,CAdoptee's fight against systemic
OL,4,Cadoption stigma
OL,6,FAs a clinical psychologist, one of the
OL,7,Ffirst questions Chris Tennyson asks
OL,8,Fhis patients is about their family
OL,9,Fmedical history. It's a question which
OL,10,Fcarries a personal irony as for
OL,11,Fdecades it's a question Chris couldn't
OL,12,Fanswer himself.
OL,14,FAdopted as a young infant, his
OL,15,Fadoptive family never received any
OL,16,Ffamily health history, a situation
OL,17,Fwhich as Chris found out, could have
OL,18,Fbeen life threatening. Chris's birth
OL,19,Fdad had a life threatening
OL,20,Fcondition...and it could be hereditary.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/6
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
